  <bioghist id="aspace_e788d4dc89f3537f8bb2f90336fd4438">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The Cayuga Bird Club was founded ca. 1913. Its first secretary was Arthur A. Allen; Louis Agassiz Fuertes served as the first president. Charter members included Liberty Hyde Bailey, Martha Van Rensselaer, Prof. William A. Stocking, Mynderse Van Cleef, and Prof. Walter F. Willcox.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_54f5a21da75e6a1c73e7342dabb6dd7e">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Minutes, correspondence, financial records, clippings, photographs, and printed material concerning the Cayuga Bird Club. Includes the club's constitution (ca. 1913) and papers of incorporation (1914); Arthur Allen's article "Cayuga Bird Club," which provides an early history of the Club and was probably published in <title>Bird Lore</title>; and correspondence of Louis Agassiz Fuertes, the club's first president, including letters to him from Jared T. Newman concerning Renwick Woodland improvement. Also, newsletters, 1989-1997, by-laws, newspaper clippings, membership lists, and receipts.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_b2aaf1f328968041250154af948d34ed">
    <head>RELATED MATERIAL</head>
<p>Related collections: Hugh Daniel Reed Papers, #2183 and Arthur A. Allen Papers, #218255.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <prefercite id="aspace_8376fb4a5150fefa74837e72664bb2a7">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Cayuga Bird Club Records, #1996. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_2d7ef244e4644a2dc6621882909d90e4">
    <head>PROVENANCE</head>
<p>The papers of the Cayuga Bird Club were part of the original Arthur A. Allen accession.</p>  </acqinfo>
